The paper deals with the problem of subgraph enumeration in large data graphs, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and has applications in various fields such as social network analysis, bioinformatics, and web mining. The paper presents two algorithms for this problem and analyzes their I/O complexity. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.DB (Databases), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
